NOTICE OF ASSOCIATION ASSESSMENT LIEN
PURSUANT TO A.R.S. $ 33-1256 OR $ 33-1807
Country Place Community Master Association, an Arizona Nonprofit Corporation ("Association"), hereby gives notice that,
pursuant to A.R.S. $ 33-1256 or $ 33-1807, the Association has a lien for assessments (and potentially other amounts
allowed by law) pursuant to the Associations Declaration of Covenants and Restrictions ('Declaration'), which was
recorded as Document Number 2000-0854140 on November 6, 2000 in the Maricopa County Recorder's Office under
Article 7, Section 7.1.
1. The legal description of the unit against which the lien exists (the "Unit") is Lot 91, Country Place Phase 2B Parcel
25, according to Book 637 of Maps, Page 29, Records of Maricopa County, Arizona.
a. Commonly known as:
9738 W Riverside Avenue
Tolleson, AZ 85353
2. The owner of the Unit, according to the Association's records, is:
Yesenia Castaneda, Jose E. Castaneda Jr
3. The amount of the lien, as of July 08, 2021, is: $829.00.
The amount of the lien may increase as set forth in the Declaration and A.R.S. $ 33-1256 or $ 33-1807
until it is satisfied in full.
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, I have hereunto set my hand this.
July
2021.
By:
Jarred Greene, the Managing Agent of Country Place Community
Master Association
State of Arizona
County of Maricopa
